</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35C48E8FFAFFFD3F4CCF931FA62AA0E" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" type="key">
<key id="FFD74C52FFAFFFD3F4CCF931FA62AA0E" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCF931FB68A509" blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" box="[136,1184,1788,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCF931FB68A509" box="[136,1184,1788,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyStep id="30B203C6FFAFFFD3F4CCF931FB68A509" box="[136,1184,1788,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">1a. Fruit elliptic to suborbicular, strongly angustiseptate silicles; ovules 6−14 per ovary; seeds uniseriate.</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<keyStep id="30B203C6FFAFFFD3F4CCF8D5FA63A573" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCF8D5FA63A535" blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" box="[136,1451,1817,1839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCF8D5FA63A535" box="[136,1451,1817,1839]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
2a. Plants pubescent; fruit valves smooth; petals 
<quantity id="4CBEB686FFAFFFD3F6C0F8D5FD2EA534" box="[644,742,1817,1839]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.0">1−1.5 mm</quantity>
long; at least some leaves pinnatifid .................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F16DF8D6FA63A535" authorityName="Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1321,1451,1817,1839]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="andraeana">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F16DF8D6FA63A535" box="[1321,1451,1817,1839]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">L. andraeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCF8FAFA63A573" blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCF8FAFA63A573" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
2b. Plants glabrous to subglabrous; fruit valves conspicuously reticulate; petals 
<quantity id="4CBEB686FFAFFFD3F7EFF8FAFC33A557" box="[939,1019,1846,1868]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2−3 mm</quantity>
long; all leaves usually entire ....................... ........................................................................................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F16DF898FA63A573" authorityName="Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1321,1451,1875,1897]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="humistrata">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F16DF898FA63A573" box="[1321,1451,1875,1897]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">L. humistrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCF8BCFB1FA59D" blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" box="[136,1239,1904,1926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCF8BCFB1FA59D" box="[136,1239,1904,1926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyStep id="30B203C6FFAFFFD3F4CCF8BCFB1FA59D" box="[136,1239,1904,1926]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">1b. Fruit oblong or linear, subterete or slightly angustiseptate siliques; ovules 20−70 per ovary; seeds biseriate.</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<keyStep id="30B203C6FFAFFFD3F4CCF841FB36A5C7" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCF841FA63A5A5" blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCF841FA63A5A5" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
3a. Fruit oblong to ellipsoid, 
<quantity id="4CBEB686FFAFFFD3F583F840FDE2A5B9" box="[455,554,1932,1954]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2−2.5 mm</quantity>
wide; ovules 20−40 per ovary; cauline leaves broadly spatulate to obovate, 3−5-lobed........... .................................................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F143F866FA63A5A5" authorityName="Edginton, Al-Shehbaz &amp; Lysak" authorityYear="2022" box="[1287,1451,1961,1983]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="queenslandica">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F143F866FA63A5A5" box="[1287,1451,1961,1983]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">L. queenslandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCF80AFB36A5C7" blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" box="[136,1278,1990,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCF80AFB36A5C7" box="[136,1278,1990,2012]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
3b. Fruit linear, 
<quantity id="4CBEB686FFAFFFD3F50DF80AFE75A5C7" box="[329,445,1990,2012]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="0.6">0.6−1.4 mm</quantity>
wide; ovules 50−70 per ovary; cauline leaves narrowly oblanceolate, (3−)5−15-lobed.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30B203C6FFAFFFD3F4CCF82FFA62AA0E" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCF82FFA62A5E3" blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" box="[136,1450,2019,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCF82FFA62A5E3" box="[136,1450,2019,2041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
4a. Plants pilose throughout; petals 2.5–4 × 
<quantity id="4CBEB686FFAFFFD3F612F82FFD7FA5E3" box="[598,695,2019,2040]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="0.9">0.9–2 mm</quantity>
........................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F169F828FA62A5E3" authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="1965" baseAuthorityName="Mueller" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[1325,1450,2019,2041]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eremigena">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F169F828FA62A5E3" box="[1325,1450,2019,2041]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">L. eremigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF91B63FFAFFFD3F4CCF7CCFA62AA0E" blockId="2.[136,1451,1788,2070]" box="[136,1450,2048,2070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<keyLead id="30B7B856FFAFFFD3F4CCF7CCFA62AA0E" box="[136,1450,2048,2070]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
4b. Plants glabrous; petals 1.4–2.2 × 
<quantity id="4CBEB686FFAFFFD3F656F7CCFD4DAA0E" box="[530,645,2048,2069]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" unit="mm" value="0.55" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.7 mm</quantity>
.............................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4660E0FFAFFFD3F159F7CCFA62AA0E" box="[1309,1450,2048,2069]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Lemphoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procumbens">
<emphasis id="B932C771FFAFFFD3F159F7CCFA62AA0E" box="[1309,1450,2048,2069]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">L. procumbens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
